  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to compare the time of home discharge in day-case patients receiving
      either a spinal anesthesia or a combined sciatic-femoral nerve block for knee arthroscopy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Two groups: the first receive a spinal anesthesia injecting 2% hyperbaric prilocaine 40 mg
      with the patients in lateral decubitus and the surgical limb declive, the second a combined
      ultrasound-guided sciatic-femoral nerve block injecting 25 ml of 2% mepivacaine solution.

      Onset time, performance time, duration of the block, time of voiding, as well as the time of
      home discharge will be evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
